If I had to articulate the bull case: The Fed is mid-pivot and the market knows it. They are as committed to a functioning banking system as to inflation. Inflation is trending downwards anyways. The effects of higher rates become more pronounced over time so economic data will likely come in weak but be accompanied by even lower inflation. This could lead to a Goldilocks period where the market is looking forward to lower rates and can shrug off poor data just as long as inflation is trending downward.
